# Release & Milestone Governance

**Project maintainer policy** (not part of the blackhole plugin protocol).

## Milestone ↔ release contract

- Each open semver milestone (`v0.4.1`, `v0.4.2`, …) maps **1:1** to a GitHub release tag `vX.Y.Z`.
- **Close a milestone only after** its matching release is published — never before.
- **Never** close a milestone without going through the create-release workflow.

## Required workflow

When all issues on milestone `vX.Y.Z` are done:

1. Follow [`.github/skills/create-release/SKILL.md`](../skills/create-release/SKILL.md):
   `bun run release prepare|validate|tag|push` with `.github/releases/vX.Y.Z.md`
2. Verify: `gh release view vX.Y.Z` — body matches the notes file
3. Close the milestone (after release is live):
   ```bash
   # Verify no open issues remain
   gh issue list --milestone "vX.Y.Z" --state open
   # Close by milestone number (from gh api repos/.../milestones or GitHub UI)
   gh api -X PATCH repos/CorentinLumineau/blackhole/milestones/{number} -f state=closed
   ```

## Anti-patterns (blocked)

- Manual `gh release create` without a committed `.github/releases/vX.Y.Z.md`
- Closing a milestone while open issues remain (unless explicitly descoped)
- Cutting a release tag that does not match the milestone semver being closed
- Retagging or force-pushing tags without user approval

## Campaign scope alignment

When running blackhole against a milestone, set `scope_milestone` in `.blackhole/config.json` to the **same** semver title. Finish the campaign, then cut the release and close the milestone in one maintainer pass.
